testItems.itemName: Do not smoke or do drugs
Eat vegetables, fruits and fibre containing food
Maintain standard body weight and do physical exercise
Avoid sugar containing food or junk food
Gurgle with tepid water after use of steroid containing inhaler.
Don't use medication without consulting with your physicians
Take glass of water/saline after each loose stool
Avoid sudden stressful activity like weight lifting, exercise
Keep your feet clean and dry
keep your body weight at a healthy level to avoid putting additional stress on joints
Do regular weight-bearing exercise (eg, jogging, walking, dancing).
Do not use pain killer or steroid medication without physician's advice
Change posture in every two hours
Sit upright for about an hour after eating. Try to eat a few hours before going to bed.
Avoid tight clothing or belts around your stomach.
Take your iron tablets with orange juice to aid absorption.
Wear earplugs when swimming to avoid recurrence of otitis externa.
Do not to scratch the ear or poke things such as cotton swabs inside the ear canal to stop the itching.
Try to avoid the known trigger factors for seizures
Avoid sitting for long periods, and take regular breaks on long journeys.
Apply a hot water bottle or heating pad to relieve the pain during periods
Stop medication on any severe events
Avoid iron containing foods eg. Liver, red meat, egg yolk etc
Consult with your physician in any emergency
Go for regular physical check up and lab investigations
Do not go for unprotected sex
Exclusively Breastfeed your baby for 6 months
Take break while working in front of computers
Give extra amount of food during pregnancy
